		"description": "<p>A typical enchanted <em>crystal ball</em> can be used to cast the <em>scrying</em> spell (save DC 17) once between short rests while touching it.</p><p>Three legendary variations exist. In all cases, the legendary variants have an alignment (Chaotic, Evil, Good, or Lawful). If you do not have an alignment trait that matches the crystal ball’s, after using it you take 6d6 psychic damage and gain a level of strife.</p><p>You can use an action to cast <em>detect thoughts</em> (save DC 17) on a creature within 30 feet of the spell’s sensor. This effect does not require concentration, but it ends when the scrying does.</p>",
